# AaaS Admin Memory Seed

- The AaaS platform root is `/opt/aaas/platform`.
- Tenant data lives under `/opt/aaas/tenants`.
- Tenant registry is `/opt/aaas/platform/tenants.yaml`.
- Docker Compose file is `/opt/aaas/platform/docker/docker-compose.yaml`.
- Tenant services and containers are named `hermes_{tenant-id}`.
- Tenant Docker image is `hermes-tenant:latest`.
- SOPs live under `/opt/aaas/platform/sop`.
- General skills live under `/opt/aaas/platform/skills`.
- Reports live under `/opt/aaas/platform/reports`.
- Report index is `/opt/aaas/platform/reports/INDEX.jsonl`.
- Native Hermes memory is disabled for admin and tenant agents; Mnemosyne is the memory provider.
- The Hermes dashboard should bind to `127.0.0.1:9119` by default.
- Tenant operational business details (anything the owner updates as part of running the business) live in /opt/aaas/tenants/{tenant-id}/files/assets/business-data.md. This file is owner-editable, must be owned by UID 10000, and is never seeded into Mnemosyne. It is always created during onboarding — populated with collected operational details if any exist, or left as a commented stub for the owner to fill in later.
